    What is Timothée Chalamet ethnicity?
    Timothée's paternal grandmother, who had moved to France, was originally Canadian. On his mother's side, he is a nephew of husband-and-wife filmmakers and producers Rodman Flender and Amy Lippman. Chalamet is bilingual in English and French, and holds dual United States and French citizenship due to his French father.

    About

    Description

    Timothée Hal Chalamet is an American and French actor. He has received various accolades, including nominations for an Academy Award, three Golden Globe Awards, and three BAFTA Film Awards. Chalamet began his career as a teenager in television, appearing in the drama series Homeland in 2012. Wikipedia
    Born: December 27, 1995 (age 28 years), New York, NY
    Parents: Marc Chalamet, Nicole Flender
    Height: 5′ 10″
    Upcoming movie: Dune: Part Two
    Siblings: Pauline Chalamet
    Alma mater: Columbia University; New York University
